# Re-arm gpsd when the u-blox GNSS receiver (re)enumerates on USB.
#
# After a USB re-enumeration gpsd keeps running but stops exporting time to its
# NTP SHM segment (unit 0), starving chrony's NMEA refclock. Because the GPIO
# PPS source is "lock NMEA", PPS then goes unusable too and chrony falls back to
# internet servers (stratum 3) until gpsd is restarted. The stock gpsdctl@
# hotplug path is insufficient here (static-device gpsd holds a stale fd), so we
# force a full gpsd restart on device 'add'.
#
# PPS is on a GPIO pin (pps@12 -> /dev/pps-gps), which is STABLE across USB
# re-enumeration, so chrony's PPS fd stays valid and re-locks automatically once
# NMEA returns. chrony is therefore intentionally NOT restarted (avoids stepping
# the clock on every USB blip).
#
# idVendor/idProduct below are for a u-blox 8 (1546:01a8). For a different
# receiver, find yours with: lsusb  (or `udevadm info -a -n /dev/ttyACM0`).
ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="tty", ATTRS{idVendor}=="1546", ATTRS{idProduct}=="01a8", TAG+="systemd", ENV{SYSTEMD_WANTS}="gps-rearm.service"
